<A Href="http://pub16.ezboard.com/bistormer"> <img src="http://members.home.net/vb6/gemini.gif" border="0"> </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uulaian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulaian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Whore</span><br> <font color=#000033>(11/13/01 5:40:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1696.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CT &amp; Demi aggro and the TRK 11/12 raid, input needed</span><hr size=1> Honestly, much of this seems to me like a person having feigned when things went bad and later got up without /q-ing to clear agro. Coupled with a few people not on the raid possibly causing some agro.<br>
<br>
However, the hailing thing for CT seems rather far fetched to me, every time i've been to fear with CT up (probably like 10 times now, for new CT) people tend to hail when they see him, never caused any problems at all. I have a few times pulled fear with a full spawn (being draco, all 3 demis, and CT), and never saw any weird agro concerning hails.<br>
<br>
A few comments though. If you moved to the base of Terror's hill, you're in the graveyard area. There are some roaming mobs here, which could explain the imp. Its a bad place to fight, better to pull Terror back to the frightfinger house. <br>
<br>
Also, in that position you're getting pretty close to the glare lord bridge, and I would not rule out the possibility of chain agroing some of them when you bring out an entire raid to that location. Won't happen for high level people, as the agro range reduces a lot with level, but have a few 46s in the mix so close to a large amount of mobs, and you're asking for trouble.<br>
<br>
Also a note on pathing, which I imagine is the reason you had GLs at the portal. Pathing for mobs that lose agro near the zone walls (due to someone dying or feigning there) is pretty screwed up in several places. For instance when pulling temple, if you feign in the wrong place the entire temple will path along the entire length of the west wall from north to south, before heading back home. On the east end of the south wall, mob can path westwards for quite a while along the wall before returning home.<br>
<br>
Anyways, not being there of course I have no way of telling exactly which of these, if any, applies to what happened, but hopefully these theories can help you in figuring it out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
